Iterative Solution - O(n) Time and O(1) Space
Factorial is computed by multiplying all integers from 1 to n using a loop. 
We initialize a variable ans as 1 and update it in each iteration by multiplying with the current number. 
This approach avoids recursion and uses constant extra space.


class GfG {

    public static int factorial(int n) {
        
        // Calculating factorial of number
        int ans = 1;
        for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
            ans = ans * i;
        }
        return ans;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        int num = 5;
        System.out.println( factorial(5));
    }
}


