Recursive Solution - O(n) Time and O(n) Space
Factorial is defined recursively as n! = n × (n - 1)!. 
We define a base case where if n equals 0 or 1, the function returns 1. 
Otherwise, the function calls itself with n minus 1, breaking the problem into smaller subproblems until reaching the base case.


class GFG {

    static int factorial(int n)
    {
        // Calculating factorial of number
        if (n == 0 || n == 1)
            return 1;
        return n * factorial(n - 1);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        int num = 5;
        System.out.println(factorial(num));
    }
}
